The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India take 4-2 lead over Pakistan

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Spearheaded by leading Indian amateurs Anirban Lahiri, Joseph Chakola, Simarjeet Singh and Jasjeet Singh, defending champions India took a commanding 4-2 lead over Pakistan after Day I of the Ravi Kirloskar Trophy meet in Islamabad on Friday. The quartet put India 2-0 up after winning the four-ball better ball format. 

Former Asian golf medallist Amit Luthra and Vinay Goel, playing in the over-40 category, made it 3-0 in Indias favour. However Rajendra Dutta and Yogesh Chopra lost their match and the score became 3-1. 

In the over 50-category, Vijay Kumar and Vikramjit Singh lost their match to the legendary Pakistan pro Taimur Hassan and his partner. Indias lead was reduced to 3-2. 

Sanjeev Talwar and IPS Mann then won their match in the same category to make it 4-2 for India. 




